edu.biu.scapi.midLayer.ciphertext

Class ByteArraySymCiphertext

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.biu.scapi.midLayer.ciphertext.ByteArraySymCiphertext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SymmetricCiphertext, java.io.Serializable

    public class ByteArraySymCiphertext
extends java.lang.Object
implements SymmetricCiphertext, java.io.Serializable
    This class represents the most basic symmetric ciphertext. It is a data holder for the ciphertext calculated by some symmetric encryption algorithm.

    It only holds the actual "ciphered" bytes and not any additional information like for example in El Gamal encryption.

    Author:
    Cryptography and Computer Security Research Group Department of Computer Science Bar-Ilan University (Yael Ejgenberg)
